  "text": "We obtained the records of average depth of the Laranjinha River at the Santa Teresa hydrometric station (downstream of Corredeira Dam) and examined the period from October 1970 to November of 2010. The monthly average depth was calculated and found to range between 0.88 and 5.68 m (Figure 4) . The historical series showed seven occasions when the level of the river was greater than the dam height and eight other occasions when river level was less than 1 m below maximum dam height (4.9 m). All graphical representations were based on K = 2. Colors represent the probability membership coefficient of that individual (column) for each genetic cluster. RAPD data plots are estimates of K group numbers based on the delta K statistic [CITATION_1] . S1, Individuals from the upstream site; S2, individuals from the downstream site.",
